        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 5:00PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 500 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Logan. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Junction City and New Straitsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
